Type: Package
Package: LLMRagent
Title: Reproducible Language-Model Agents for Research
Version: 0.8.0
Authors@R:
    person("Ali", "Sanaei", , "sanaei@uchicago.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Build language-model agents in R on top of the 'LLMR' package. The
  run object, manifest, archive, and tool-policy checks carry reproducibility and
  governance through the workflow. An agent works
  from a persona, calls native R tools, keeps memory, and stays within a
  declared budget. Several agents converse over a shared transcript under a
  turn-taking policy, which supplies presets for debates, focus groups,
  interviews, and deliberations with votes; factorial experiments over those
  designs run in parallel and return tidy results. Every run converts to one
  object that exposes utterance, event, call, tool, and state views, a study
  manifest of content hashes, and a sealed replication archive whose call log
  reads back through 'LLMR'. Governance covers declared tool side effects,
  guardrails on inputs, outputs, and tool results, human approval gates that
  pause and resume, and diagnostics for state leakage. Validity helpers provide
  robustness checks across prompt and model perturbations, calibration with
  design-based and prediction-powered estimation from imperfect labels,
  anti-essentialist persona checks, and claim types that restrict
  population-level language unless calibration is attached. A small workflow runtime adds checkpoint, resume, fork,
  and replay. Optional layers provide a governed Model Context Protocol client,
  sandboxed tool execution, social-simulation scaffolding, and an HTML run
  inspector.
